me-1 pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dkYRCH hYpqjU"><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-125_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-126_"><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-127_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Every year, on July 11th, the world comes together to observe World Population Day. It's a day dedicated to raising awareness about global population issues, promoting reproductive health and rights, and advocating for sustainable solutions to address population challenges. With our planet's population steadily increasing, understanding the implications of this growth is crucial for building a better future for all.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-129_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-130_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-131_ pf-heading-1-h3">Defining World Population Day</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/hands-holding-earth-csr-business-campaign-2023-11-27-05-05-53-utc.jpg?v=1709546100" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/hands-holding-earth-csr-business-campaign-2023-11-27-05-05-53-utc.jpg?v=1709546100 1536w" width="1000" height="667" alt="Navigating the Future: The Impact of World Population Day 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Navigating the Future: The Impact of World Population Day 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-133_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-134_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-136_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">World Population Day, established by the United Nations, serves as a platform to highlight the importance of addressing population challenges. It emphasises the need for comprehensive strategies that promote reproductive health, empower women and girls, and ensure sustainable development for future generations.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-138_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-139_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-140_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_3065f4e9-e7fe-438c-acd3-d80dbedff30b.png?v=1709366402" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_3065f4e9-e7fe-438c-acd3-d80dbedff30b.png?v=1709366402 1536w" width="1419" height="946" alt="2024 and Beyond: Strategies for Sustainable Population Growth - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="2024 and Beyond: Strategies for Sustainable Population Growth - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-142_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-143_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by mohdizzuanbinroslan via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-145_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-146_ pf-text-1">As of 2024, the global population stands at over 7.8 billion people and is projected to reach 9.7 billion by 2050.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-148_ pf-text-1">Population growth rates vary across regions, with some experiencing rapid growth while others face declining populations.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-150_ pf-text-1">Overpopulation can strain resources, contribute to environmental degradation, and exacerbate social and economic inequalities.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-152_ pf-text-1">Access to reproductive health services, including family planning and contraception, remains a challenge for many individuals worldwide.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-154_ pf-text-1">Gender equality and women's empowerment are essential aspects of addressing population issues and promoting sustainable development.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-156_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-157_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-158_ pf-heading-1-h3">Organisations making a difference</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/the-shibuya-crossing-2023-11-27-05-27-30-utc.jpg?v=1709546257" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/the-shibuya-crossing-2023-11-27-05-27-30-utc.jpg?v=1709546257 1536w" width="1000" height="620" alt="Empowering Change: The Role of Education on World Population Day 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Empowering Change: The Role of Education on World Population Day 2024 - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-160_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-161_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-163_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-164_ pf-text-1"><b>United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA)</b> - Leading global efforts to advance reproductive health and rights, UNFPA plays a central role in coordinating World Population Day activities.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-166_ pf-text-1"><b>Population Matters</b> - A UK-based charity advocating for sustainable population size, Population Matters raises awareness of the impacts of population growth on the environment and human well-being.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-168_ pf-text-1"><b>Marie Stopes International</b> - Providing reproductive healthcare services worldwide, Marie Stopes International works to empower individuals with access to family planning and contraception.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-170_ pf-text-1"><b>Government Agencies</b> - Government bodies such as the Department for International Development (DFID) and the Foreign, Commonwealth &amp; Development Office (FCDO) support initiatives to address population challenges through international development efforts.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-172_ pf-text-1"><b>The Mandatory Training Group</b> - As a leading UK provider of World Population Day-related content, The Mandatory Training Group offers valuable resources and solutions to educate and empower individuals on population issues.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-174_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-175_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-176_ pf-heading-1-h3">Engaging learners</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/being-successful-standing-out-from-the-crowd-lea-2023-11-27-05-22-02-utc.jpg?v=1709546526" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/being-successful-standing-out-from-the-crowd-lea-2023-11-27-05-22-02